-- Skoda Auto Aims to Double Production in 10 Years, Hospodarske Noviny Says
-- B y   L a d k a   B a u e r o v a
-- 2010-09-24T05:26:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-24/skoda-auto-aims-to-double-production-in-10-years-hospodarske-noviny-says.html
Skoda Auto AS, the Czech unit of
Volkswagen AG, aim to at least double its annual production
within the next 10 years to 1.5 million cars, Hospodarske Noviny
reported, citing Chairman Winfried Vahland.  The carmaker plans to boost its sales in emerging markets
such as China, India, Russia and eastern Europe, the newspaper
said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ladka Bauerova at 
 lbauerova@bloomberg.net  